Brilliant dinosaur set for dino enthusiasts. They are life-like and great for boys and girls aged 3 years old and up. It is an excellent educational toy that will teach your children cooperation with their friends or will keep them creatively entertained in their own room! Recommended educational toys for boys ages 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8.

In the process of assemble dinosaurs with tools, it can exercise the kids hands-on ability.

Safe and Funny Building Toys: We used premium materials during production because we know you want only the best for your kids. The dinosaur toys made of sturdy and non-toxic ABS material, smooth edges and right size is suitable for children to build up. Kids can follow the instructions to build a complete dinosaur, or they can put different parts together according to their ideas.

Gifts for 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8 year old Toddler Boys Girls: We are so confident that your kids would like our dinosaur gift for boys and girls. Highly recommend for 3-8 yr old kids toddler.It is perfect gifts for dinosaur themed party, Christmas, Children's Day, birthday,Thanksgiving Day, Easter. Never go wrong as a gift!

reviews.reviewText: We just bought these for our 4 year old grandson for his birthday. He absolutely loves them and is takes the power screwdriver toy with him wherever he goes. Even his big sisters, age 8 and 10, like to build the dinosaurs. I would definitely recommend and I would buy again.

reviews.reviewText: I bought this for my 4 year old nephew. He loves tools and dinosaurs and STEM type projects, so this toy fit all categories. He is homeschooling in Pre-K, so this toy is very functional to use as play, pretend, and for learning. He loves it!

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A little difficult to assemble
reviews.reviewText: This was given to two 5 year olds. Too difficult for them to assemble. Mom and Dad took a while to assemble. Kids loved them when assembled.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I bought this set for a 4 and a 6 year old to entertain them while the adults socialized. We had to help them to build the set as instructed the first time but then they assembled and disassembled them creating hybrids. I bought two sets from two different manufacturers. There was very little difference. This set didn't have little wheels underneath the feet but the difference didn't bother the kids in the least. I liked the screw drivers that were in this set. They were colorful and easy to handle. The kids never used the screw drivers. They only used the battery operated drills. It takes 2 AAA batteries. The pieces were interchangeable between the two sets. This sets dinosaurs were slightly larger, not significantly though. Great for increasing problem solving skills and small motor skills.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars NOT for 3 year old
reviews.reviewText: These are super cute, but most definitely NOT for a 3 year old. There are a thousand pieces and there's no way they can stay entertained long enough to go through directions and put these together. My husband put them all together while my son tried to "help" by taking the screws and nearly losing all of them.It would be a long shot for even my 6 year old nephew to put these together without a lot of assistance. I would say these would be perfect for 8/9/10 year olds.

A bit too difficult for a 3 or 4 year old. Will definitely need an adult to assist with the build of the figures. The packaging it comes in could be better if this was purchased as a present for someone. Great DIY /Build-it-yourself starter kit for children and definitely suitable for both girls and boys.
The kids enjoyed building these however the box was damaged & not suitable for gift giving.

reviews.reviewTitle: Good but too hard for kids to put together
reviews.reviewText: Needs improvement with the instructions. Good quality toys, children aged 7 and below will need help from parents to put this toys together.
We bought two sets for our twin grandsons. They are really enjoying them. Unfortunately, one set came with two left back legs for the red triceratops!!!
